author: Multiple contributors from Cagayancillo, Palawan
notes: This word list was collected by translator Jacqueline Andrea Huggins while living among the Kagayanen people and conducting linguistic research from August 1987 until September 2003.
classification: Austronesian, Malayo-Polynesian, Philippine, Greater Central Philippine, Manobo, North

author: hand
glottocode: Also five; Regular [l] always contiguous with high front vowel [i]

author: left
glottocode: [ð] for the interdental lateral approximant has diacritic underneath for tongue raising; sound is under discussion to be added to the IPA

author: to swim
glottocode: To take a bath/swim; also [lúoy] for swim

author: to know, be knowledgeable
glottocode: Interdental lateral approximant; use diacritic for lenghtning

author: head
glottocode: Interdental lateral approximant with tongue lengthening diacritic.

author: to sleep
glottocode: also has the variants, tunuga     and tinuga to disambiguate meanings

author: to split
glottocode: (to split something in half like bread, an orange, or to split  a                      coconut in half with a machete)

author: to split
glottocode: (to chop with an ax or machete is used only with reference to wood)

author: to fall
glottocode: to fall or keel over as if in a dead faint

author: dry
glottocode: (things that were wet but become dry)
